    {
      "id": 14,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [-1040, 40],
      "size": [360, 520],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 13,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# Anima 360 Angle Control\n\nUse the yaw slider for the horizontal angle: 0 front, 90 right profile, 180 back, 270 left profile. Pitch controls low/high angle, roll tilts the camera, and zoom controls framing.\n\nThe custom JS extension draws a live OpenPose preview inside the angle node before queueing. The generated OpenPose-style guide is also VAE-encoded. `Anima Apply Reference Latent` attaches that latent to the positive and negative conditioning as `reference_latents`, then the Qwen Union Control LoRA uses it as structural guidance.\n\nRequired models:\n- diffusion_models/anima-base-v1.0.safetensors\n- text_encoders/qwen_3_06b_base.safetensors\n- vae/qwen_image_vae.safetensors\n- loras/qwen_image_union_diffsynth_lora.safetensors\n\nIf the angle is weak, keep the prompt simple, leave denoise at 1.0, raise LoRA strength slightly, or make the guide lines thicker."
      ],
      "color": "#222",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    }
